						               													<description>Accept and present demanding personal challenges, moral obligations and financial considerations.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players attempt to build a viable, ' friendly ' financial empire within the constraints of a constantly changing inflation mechanism whilst resisting player takeover bids and personal challenges.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Unlike Monopoly, Cash Flow allows for all players to         ' be in the game ' at all times, even when they are without assets or cash.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players are always participants rather than just seat dwellers; unlike Monopoly when one person gets ahead.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Intriguing challenge cards allow players to constantly challenge each other player, at any time, thereby Cash Flow is not just about cash management and acquisition.  &amp;#10;  &amp;#10;Players are also personally challenged to develop or destroy personal relationships, within a time limit constraint, rather than employ a &amp;quot;one grabs all&amp;quot; style.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Even the most modest underdog can get up and win like the proverbial hawk / phoenix.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Number 1 selling game in South Australia during its limited Australian Release.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Cash Flow sold across South Australia and Interstate       ( QLD, NSW &amp;amp; VIC ) and still holds the auspicious record of selling 10,000+ games in just over 2 weeks.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The local market was designed and in place to support the overseas promotion / marketing of the game; based solely on the South Australian test market results, Cash Flow was assigned under master licensee over 6 continents, within one year of making its test market debut - making it one of Australia's most successful games ever.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
